</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>You can watch the new Dawn of War 4 Mechanicus trailer here.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6qZMz4nrTOg" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>The Adeptus Mechanicus is a fast-paced, tech-heavy army with a lot of powerful ranged combat options. They also have access to plenty of cool mechanised vehicles, as you'd expect from a gaggle of religiously-inclined engineers.</p>
<p>This gameplay trailer comes roughly two weeks after the faction got its own CGI trailer, setting the tone for what they're about with a brief delve into a Necron cavern. With this gameplay trailer, Dawn of War 4 fans have been able to see two factions in action, the first being the Orks' more rambunctious fighting style.</p><p>Dawn of War 4, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/warhammer-40k-dawn-of-war-4-announced-and-its-coming-from-a-surprise-new-developer-next-year">first announced during last year's Gamescom Opening Night Live</a>, is a much-anticipated sequel, especially given the <em>so-so</em> reception to <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/warhammer-40000-dawn-war-3">Dawn of War 3</a>. If you fancy an idea of what it's like to play, you can read <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/ive-played-warhammer-40k-dawn-of-war-4-and-it-feels-like-the-sequel-to-the-original-that-rts-fans-always-wanted">our early preview for a glimpse of what's to come later this year</a>.</p>

